  "prompt": "How do you know who viewed you video on Instagram?",
  "response": "Instagram does not provide a direct way to see exactly who has viewed your video. Here's what you can see:\n\n1. For Instagram Stories:\n- You can see a list of viewers by swiping up on your story\n- Viewers are listed in the order they viewed\n- Only the number and usernames of people who viewed are shown\n\n2. For regular Instagram Posts/Reels:\n- You can see the total number of views\n- You cannot see individual viewers\n\n3. Instagram Insights (for Business/Creator accounts):\n- Provides more detailed analytics about video performance\n- Shows view count, engagement metrics\n- Does not reveal individual viewer identities\n\n4. Third-party apps claiming to show viewers are typically unreliable and may violate Instagram's terms of service.\n\nSo while you can see view counts and analytics, Instagram intentionally does not allow users to see a detailed list of who viewed regular posts or reels.",
